      "source": [
        "## **HEALTH INSURANCE PREMIUM PREDICTION USING RANDOM FOREST**\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tln6wUnopTy2"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**1. PROBLEM SPECIFICATION**\n",
        "\n",
        "**1.1 Objective**\n",
        "\n",
        "Predict individual medical insurance costs (*charges*) based on demographic and health-related features.\n",
        "\n",
        "**1.2 Why this matters**\n",
        "\n",
        "Accurate prediction of insurance charges is central to:\n",
        "\n",
        "*Risk-based pricing*: insurers set premiums according to expected cost\n",
        "*Risk segmentation*: identifying high-risk vs low-risk policyholders\n",
        "*Cost control*: understanding key drivers of healthcare expenditure\n",
        "\n",
        "Without reliable estimates, insurers either underprice (losses) or overprice (lose customers).\n",
        "\n",
        "**1.3 Type of problem**\n",
        "\n",
        "Supervised learning, regression task\n",
        "Target variable (charges) is continuous.\n",
        "\n",
        "**1.4 Evaluation metrics**\n",
        "\n",
        "*MAE (Mean Absolute Error)*: Measures average absolute deviation between predicted and actual charges.\n",
        "\n",
        "*   Easy to interpret in dollar terms\n",
        "*   Less sensitive to extreme outliers\n",
        "\n",
        "*RMSE (Root Mean Squared Error)*: Penalizes larger errors more heavily.\n",
        "Useful because:\n",
        "\n",
        "*   Highlights poor performance on high-cost individuals\n",
        "*   Aligns with risk concerns in insurance (large claims matter more)\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "RYranTQJphW-"
      }
    },
