    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Interesting. “smoker” status is by far the most important feature in our model. “bmi” and “age” are moderately important as well. This confirms some of the information we got from our correlation heatmap previously. The features which had the higher correlations with the target are unsurprisingly the ones with higher importance in the model’s predictive performance."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "iBzD9hBhQ_7S"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**6. HYPERPARAMETER TUNING**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "II5yrSGz2nXx"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**6.1 Finding Optimimum Parameters**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. max_depth controls model complexity\n",
        "2. min_samples_leaf reduces overfitting\n",
        "3. n_estimators improves stability\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9Bdrvjt_3ENA"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "param_grid = {\n",
        "    \"max_depth\":[None, 2, 5],\n",
        "    \"min_samples_split\": [2, 4, 6, 8],\n",
        "    \"min_samples_leaf\": [1, 2, 4, 6]\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "model = RandomForestRegressor(n_jobs=-1)\n",
        "\n",
        "grid_search = GridSearchCV(model, param_grid=param_grid, cv=5)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pkQ8Eu9fR10u"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
